    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-08T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="1031"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1031">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/7–854: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_AWW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Aldrich</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-08T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 8, 1954—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>124. Eyes only Secretary. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 101.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d1031fn1">Dated July 7, <ref target="#pg_1788">p.
                        1788</ref>.</note> I saw <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> this
                    afternoon. He will answer your message soonest.<note n="2" xml:id="d1031fn2">In
                        his response, transmitted through Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MSR1"
                            >Makins</persName> on July 8, Foreign Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> expressed the hope that Secretary
                            <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> or Under Secretary
                            <persName corresp="#p_SGWB1">Smith</persName> would return to Geneva the
                        following week. (611.93/7–854)</note> Meanwhile he asked me to say he is
                    going to Geneva Monday,<note n="3" xml:id="d1031fn3">July 12.</note> and will
                    meet <persName corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes-France</persName>. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes-France</persName> wished him to come Paris over
                    week-end but he is unable to do this. <persName corresp="#p_ESA1"
                        >Eden</persName> will support French at Geneva in attempt to get most
                    favorable possible settlement. He has no information or idea how matter may work
                    out because Russians have not disclosed their hand and he is sure they will not
                    do so until meetings take place in Geneva. Weakness of French position is of
                    course fact that election would undoubtedly result in all Viet Nam going
                    Communist and therefore division of country in all probability best solution. It
                    is impossible to foresee how this trump card may be played by Communists.
                        <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName>
                    <pb facs="0413" n="1795" xml:id="pg_1795"/> does not think it would be fair to
                    you to expect you to attend Geneva Conference this juncture but thinks it would
                    be very helpful to him and the French if <persName corresp="#p_SGWB1"
                        >Bedell</persName> could be there and hopes that if <persName
                        corresp="#p_SGWB1">Bedell</persName> comes he will stop in London on
                    way.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Comment:</hi> I am sure <persName corresp="#p_ESA1"
                        >Eden</persName> is extremely anxious to have <persName corresp="#p_SGWB1"
                        >Bedell</persName> present because of <persName corresp="#p_SGWB1"
                        >Bedell</persName>’s intimate knowledge of personalities involved at Geneva
                    and of manner in which situation has developed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AWW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Aldrich</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
